org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.activities

Interface Optional

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    OptionalImpl

    public interface Optional
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Optional'. When the «optional» stereotype is applied to parameters, the lower multiplicity must be equal to zero. This means the parameter is not required to have a value for the activity or any behavior to begin or end execution. Otherwise, the lower multiplicity must be greater than zero, which is called “required.”

    The following features are supported:

    • Base Parameter
    See Also:
    ActivitiesPackage.getOptional()
